sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users_accessing_item
FROM access_logs
WHERE item_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'tinkered with' refers to items that were modified;
- 'write access' means the item has 'write' permission;
- 'admin credentials' indicate the role of the user who last modified the item is 'admin';
- 'category' refers to 'segment';
- 'messed with' is synonymous with 'modified'.
